@jorisvandenbossche I view `to_numeric` as basically `.astype`, with better error handling. So in that vein, I don't think it has to be `object` to begin with, though maybe we should _also_ add a `dtype=` option.

alternatively, _maybe_ add these instead to `.astype`.

and @gfyoung certainly remove the non int64-sentinels though.
